The paper deals with improving neural network training by allowing non-differentiable functions, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve image representation learning (cs.CV) and image classification (cs.CV), which further supports the inclusion of these categories. Additionally, the paper introduces a new method for training neural networks, which could also fall under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) or computational linguistics (cs.CL) depending on the specific application.
